      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Sending of `getdata` happens in the `on_inv()` callback method, i.e. as reply to an received `inv` message from the node. The `sync_with_ping`s are there to have some implicit delay to ensure there was enough time for the `inv`/`getdata` exchange and a (in this case, fictive) `merkleblock` message to arrive, so that the assert below has a value. (If you remember, we discussed in PR https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/18334 about this multiple-ping approach; I was [sceptical](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/18334#issuecomment-605617660) but [your explanation](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/18334#issuecomment-605624202) led me to the conclusion that there is no better way of doing this.)",
      "commit_id" : "c4d5ba83b2ca5781821cc288295da81156a28277",
      "created_at" : "2020-04-13T15:21:24Z",
      "diff_hunk" : "@@ -104,6 +105,18 @@ def run_test(self):\n             txid = self.nodes[0].sendtoaddress(self.nodes[0].getnewaddress(), 7)\n             filter_node.wait_for_tx(txid)\n \n+        self.log.info('Check that request for filtered blocks is ignored if no filter is set')\n+        filter_node.merkleblock_received = False\n+        self.nodes[0].generatetoaddress(1, self.nodes[0].getnewaddress())\n+        filter_node.sync_with_ping()\n+        filter_node.sync_with_ping()",
